260. The funeral ceremonies of the oriental nations are much the same at the present day as in the age of Priam. The body is usually carried by the sons; while the daughters (followed by a long train of females, sometimes brought together by affection, but more commonly hired sor the purpose) break ’out at stated intervals into piercing lamentations‚ which are instantly taken up and re-echoed by the whole proces- sion.
